data.enText: to eat grass that is growing in a field
There were cows grazing beside the river.

data.chText: 家长得到忠告不要让孩子乱吃零食。
data.enText: Parents have been warned against allowing children to graze on snacks (= to keep eating them, instead of real meals) .
The field had been grazed by sheep.
to put cows, sheep, etc. in a field so that they can eat the grass there

data.chText: 这块地当地人用来放牧。
data.enText: The land is used by local people to graze their animals.
to break the surface of your skin by rubbing it against sth rough

data.chText: 我摔了一跤擦伤了膝盖。
data.enText: I fell and grazed my knee.
to touch sth lightly while passing it
a small injury where the surface of the skin has been slightly broken by rubbing against sth

data.chText: 亚当在撞车事故中平安脱险，只受了点划伤和擦伤。
data.enText: Adam walked away from the crash with just cuts and grazes .

ex.enText: The sheep are browsing on the hillside.
The camels browsed on the trees.

synonyms.bx: 指牛、羊、鹿等吃草或高处的植物绿叶。

ex.chText: 他们决定在自己田里牧牛。
ex.enText: They decided to graze cattle in their fields.
The sheep were turned out to graze.

ex.chText: 不远处那片广阔的田地就是他们曾经放牧的地方。
ex.enText: The vast area not far away is the fields on which they used to graze.

synonyms.bx: 既可指使牲畜啃食牧草，也可指动物吃草。

ex.chText: 几个小男孩计划一起去放牛。
ex.enText: Several boys planned to pasture their cattle together.

ex.chText: 这些奶牛被放出去吃草。
ex.enText: The cows are put out to pasture.

synonyms.bx: 主要指放牧牛、马等家畜，也可指牛、羊等吃草。

example: There was so much food at the party that we quickly got sated just by browsing

tr: feed as in a meadow or pasture
let feed in a field or pasture or meadow
break the skin (of a body part) by scraping
example: She was grazed by the stray bullet

value.def: When animals graze or are grazed, they eat the grass or other plants that are growing in a particular place. You can also say that a field is grazed by animals.

example.ex: Five cows graze serenely around a massive oak...
example.tran: 5头奶牛在一棵大橡树旁悠闲自在地啃着青草。

example.ex: The hills have been grazed by sheep because they were too steep to be ploughed...
example.tran: 这几座山过于陡峭，不适于耕种，所以就用来牧羊了。
一大群正在吃草的动物

value.def: If you graze a part of your body, you injure your skin by scraping against something.

example.ex: I had grazed my knees a little.
example.tran: 我的膝盖擦破了一点皮。

value.def: A graze is a small wound caused by scraping against something.
If something grazes another thing, it touches that thing lightly as it passes by.

example.ex: A bullet had grazed his arm...
example.tran: 一颗子弹擦过他的手臂。

example.ex: Wright managed a shot but it grazed the near post and rolled harmlessly across the goal.
example.tran: 赖特勉强起脚射门，但是球擦着近门柱有惊无险地偏出了球门。
